    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1920-05-29">May 29, 1920.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear <persName key="vachel_lindsay">Lindsay</persName>:-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am afraid mysteries are not much in my line. It never seems necessary to create
                a mystery about one's self when all life is so much of a mystery. This sounds
                didactic and prudish, but nevertheless it is a fact. Are you going to be married?
                Are you going into the monastery? Are you turning missionary? For to some such
                simple fact I presume your mystery boils down, but even with a plain statement of
                the fact in question, believe me it would remain as much of a mystery as ever. You
                will tell me, I suppose, all in good time, but do not withhold the knowledge from me
                on the plea that we have had a slight acquaintance, for indeed I feel a much warmer,
                kinder friendship than that, and I hoped you did. At any rate, the very best of luck
                to your English trip, and I shall look forward to <title>“The Golden Book of Springfield”</title>
                with much interest.</p>
                <closer>Very sincerely yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
